{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "English academic writing is a complex and multi-faceted activity that requires coordinating multiple cognitive skills and knowledge to orchestrate writing processes such as facilitating goal setting, problem-solving, and strategically managing memory resources (Allen & McNamara, 2017; Flower & Hayes, 1981).",
    "The writing process is unique to each individual student; students bring their own individual characteristics, including linguistic and general literacy backgrounds, prior domain knowledge, as well as affective states (e.g., attitudes toward academic writing, engagement with the task), all of which potentially affect their performance (Gupta et al., 2022; Pineteh, 2014).",
    "This process can be even more challenging for English as a second language (ESL) students who often face language barriers.",
    "Yet, educators generally have insufficient time to offer personalized instruction and formative feedback, preventing students from having sufficient opportunities to practice writing and incorporate feedback to improve their writing experience (Aldabbus & Almansouri, 2022; Gupta et al., 2022).",
    "Pertaining to such challenges, generative artificial intelligence (GenAI)-powered writing tools have emerged to support students in their academic writing process and enhance ESL learners' writing skills."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "English academic writing is a complex and multi-faceted activity that requires coordinating multiple cognitive skills and knowledge to orchestrate writing processes such as facilitating goal setting, problem-solving, and strategically managing memory resources (Allen & McNamara, 2017; Flower & Hayes, 1981).",
